# Javi Rubio Personal Website - AI Development Guidelines

## Project Overview

Personal website for Javi Rubio - software engineer, speaker, and techno-activist. Single-page landing focused on legitimacy, presence, and showcasing speaking/community work. Built with simplicity and maintainability as core principles.

**Live site:** https://javirubio.net  
**Repository:** https://github.com/jrub/jrub-web  
**Deployed on:** Netlify

## Tech Stack & Constraints

### Core Technologies
- **Framework:** Astro (static site generation)
- **Language:** JavaScript (vanilla, NO TypeScript)
- **Styling:** CSS vanilla with CSS variables (NO Tailwind, NO CSS frameworks)
- **Fonts:** System fonts only (NO Google Fonts, NO external font services)
- **Images:** Optimized via Astro's Picture component, stored in `/src/assets/`

### What We DO NOT Use
- ❌ TypeScript
- ❌ Tailwind CSS or any CSS framework
- ❌ External dependencies beyond Astro core (exception below)
- ❌ jQuery or other legacy libraries
- ❌ Third-party analytics or tracking
- ❌ Cookie consent banners (privacy-first approach)

### Intentional Exceptions
- ✅ **`typed.js`** — kept intentionally for the typewriter role animation in the hero. Do NOT propose removing it, even though the general rule says "no external deps."

## Design Philosophy

### Core Principles
1. **KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid):** Prefer simple, understandable solutions over clever abstractions
2. **Maintainability over features:** Code should be readable and modifiable years from now
3. **No premature optimization:** Build what's needed, optimize if proven necessary
4. **Minimize dependencies:** Every dependency is a liability

### Visual Design
- **Minimalist aesthetic:** Inspired by francesc.net, danilat.com, myowncommonsense.com
- **Clean typography:** Large, readable text with clear hierarchy
- **Spacious layout:** Generous whitespace, mobile-first responsive
- **Animations:** Minimal. The photo carousel (CSS `fadeSlide`) and profile photo `fadeIn` are intentional design choices. Do NOT propose removing them. Only add new animations if explicitly requested.
- **Accessible:** Semantic HTML, keyboard navigation, proper ARIA labels

### Site Language
**The site is in English.** All UI text, button labels, aria labels, `<summary>` text, and any copy inside the HTML template must be in English — even when the planning conversation is in Spanish.

## Color Palette
```css
/* Brand colors */
--magenta: #C61E6B;      /* Primary accent, headings, CTAs */
--turquesa: #7BC5BC;     /* Secondary accent, links */

/* Neutrals */
--white: #FFFFFF;        /* Background */
--black: #1A1A1A;        /* Primary text */
--gray-light: #F8F8F8;   /* Alternate backgrounds */
--gray-mid: #666666;     /* Secondary text */
```

**Usage:**
- Magenta: h1, h2, primary buttons, hover states
- Turquesa: links, subtle accents
- Black: body text
- Grays: muted content, backgrounds

## Project Structure
```
/
├── src/
│   ├── assets/
│   │   └── photos/          # Conference/event photos (Astro-optimized)
│   ├── data/
│   │   └── speaking.json            # All speaking/community data
│   ├── layouts/
│   │   └── Layout.astro     # Base layout with header/footer
│   ├── pages/
│   │   └── index.astro      # Single-page landing (everything)
│   └── styles/
│       └── global.css       # All styles, CSS variables
├── public/
│   ├── profile.jpg          # Profile photo
│   └── favicon.ico
└── tests/
    └── *.spec.js            # Playwright tests (geometry validation)
```

## Content Strategy

### Site Structure (Single Page)
1. **Hero:** Name + profile photo
2. **About:** Bio (3 paragraphs)
3. **Public Speaking & Tech Communities:** JSON-driven sections
   - Tech Conference Talks (with hero carousel)
   - Workshops & Facilitation
   - Podcasts & Radio interviews
   - Tech Communities
4. **Footer/Contact:** Email + social links (no tagline — removed to avoid duplication with hero subtitle)

### Data-Driven Content
All speaking/community content lives in `src/data/speaking.json`. Structure:
- `talks[]`: Talks at conferences
- `workshops[]`: Workshops, courses, facilitation
- `media[]`: Radio, podcast appearances
- `communities[]`: Community work, organizing, mentoring

Each item supports:
- `featured: boolean` - Show by default vs. hidden until "Show all"
- `language: "en"|"es"` - Event language (display with badge/indicator)
- `photos[]` - Array of photos with src and caption
- `links[]` - Additional references (Twitter, articles)

## Development Guidelines

### JavaScript
- **Vanilla JS only:** No frameworks, no build-time complexity
- **ES6+ syntax:** Use modern features (const/let, arrow functions, template literals)
- **Small, focused functions:** Each function does one thing well
- **Comments for "why" not "what":** Code should be self-documenting
- **Error handling:** Always handle potential failures gracefully

### CSS
- **Mobile-first:** Write mobile styles first, desktop overrides via media queries
- **CSS variables for theming:** All colors, spacing defined as variables
- **BEM-like naming when helpful:** Use semantic class names
- **Minimal nesting:** Keep specificity low, avoid deep nesting
- **No !important unless absolutely necessary:** Fix specificity issues properly

### Commits
- **Small, atomic commits:** One logical change per commit
- **Descriptive messages:** "Fix carousel mobile layout" not "fix bug"
- **Present tense:** "Add feature" not "Added feature"
- **Reference issues when applicable:** "Fix #123: carousel overflow"

## Photo Carousel

### Current Implementation
- **Location:** Top of Speaking & Community section
- **Shows ALL photos:** Cycles through all photos from all events/items in speaking.json
- **Auto-advances:** Automatic rotation through all available photos
- **Responsive behavior:**
  - Desktop: Floats right, text wraps left
  - Mobile: Stacks above content, full width
- **Dynamic sizing:** Adapts to landscape/portrait orientation
- **Vanilla JS:** No libraries, smooth transitions
- **Tested:** Playwright tests validate layout geometry

### Carousel Features
- All photos from `speaking.json` photos arrays
- Captions with hashtags (#SCBCN25, etc.)
- Smooth transitions (0.3s fade)
- Border-radius preserved
- Must NOT break existing Playwright tests

### Individual Event Galleries
- Items with `photos[]` show "[📷 N photos]" link
- Click opens lightbox modal with carousel
- Modal carousel: same logic as hero, but manual navigation only

## Testing Requirements

### Playwright Tests
- **Location:** `/tests/*.spec.js`
- **Purpose:** Validate layout geometry, prevent regressions
- **Coverage:** Carousel positioning, spacing, responsive behavior
- **Run before deploy:** Tests must pass before merging

### Manual Testing Checklist
- [ ] All pages load without errors
- [ ] Smooth scroll navigation works
- [ ] Featured items display correctly
- [ ] "Show all/less" buttons work
- [ ] External links open in new tab
- [ ] Photos load and carousel functions
- [ ] Mobile responsive (test on actual device)
- [ ] No console errors

## Deployment

**Netlify configuration:**
- Auto-deploy from `main` branch
- Build command: `npm run build`
- Publish directory: `dist/`
- Node version: 18+

**Pre-deploy checklist:**
- [ ] Run tests: `npm test`
- [ ] Build locally: `npm run build`
- [ ] Preview build: `npm run preview`
- [ ] Check for console errors
- [ ] Verify all links work

